# Forge — AI Coding Toolkit

Apply Forge skills based on what you are doing:

- Reviewing code or a PR → forge:review
- Security concerns → forge:secure
- Architecture or system design → forge:arch
- Writing a new feature → forge:tdd (failing tests first)
- Writing docs → forge:docs
- Cleaning up code → forge:refine
- Changing an LLM feature → forge:eval
- Code quality → forge:standards

## Review finding format

```
[SEVERITY] category — title
File: path:line
Problem: one sentence
Fix: concrete action
```

Severity labels: CRITICAL / HIGH / MEDIUM / LOW
Verdicts: BLOCK / REQUEST CHANGES / APPROVE WITH NOTES / APPROVE

## Non-negotiable rules

- No hardcoded secrets
- No feature without a failing test first
- No LLM prompt change without evals
- No production mutation without explicit human confirmation
- Structured logs with traceId on every cross-boundary call
